Results\: Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching. f1f292c2-4c9b-4cb7-b7a6-433930c5ba94.b9f8421b-7a0e-43bd-9ccc-4a4242fe4abb.description=9eb5d3f1-e3b8-4c52-b55e-421b5934ee38.dfbefbe2-84b1-43a8-81a0-a32ecda3e917.description f1f292c2-4c9b-4cb7-b7a6-433930c5ba94.description=
 Purpose

This workflow will create a Weblogic Cluster from an existing installation and domain of Weblogic 11g or 12c and add existing Managed Servers to the Cluster.


 Results Verification

The Console will indicate whether the workflow completed without errors. The workflow results will indicate whether the creation was successful. 

 Notification Plan

Define who should be notified when the workflow succeeds and fails.



 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    BEA Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the product installation directory in which to install WebLogic Server. For instance /opt/oracle/WebLogic.
    Cluster Name - Required\: This will be the name that the Cluster. For example ClusterAppServer1
    Domain Path - Required\: Fully qualified path that the domain and domain configuration will be created under. For example /opt/weblogic/user_projects/domains.
    Managed Servers - Required\: Comma delimited list of managed server names. EG\: "AppServer1, AppServer2"
    Server.Become User - No description
    WLS Install Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the Middleware Home directory that will contain this installation. For instance /opt/oracle/WebLogic/wlserver_10.3

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Multicast Port - Optional\: The multicast port (between 1 and 65535) used by cluster members to communicate with each other
    Multicast Address - Optional\: The multicast address used by cluster members to communicate with each other.
